column1: 1/ Midquarter population estimates by state are derived by BEA based on unpublished Census Bureau estimates of beginning-of-month population. Quarterly estimates for 2010-2018 reflect unpublished monthly population estimates available as of February 2019.
2/ Per capita personal income is total personal income divided by total quarterly population estimates.
* Estimates prior to 1950 are not available for Alaska and Hawaii.
Note-- Millions of dollars, seasonally adjusted at annual rates. All dollar estimates are in current dollars (not adjusted for inflation). Calculations are performed on unrounded data.
Last updated: March 26, 2019-- new estimates for 2018:Q4; revised estimates for 2010:Q1-2018:Q3.
